<HEADLINE>
FT  16 NOV 94 / Survey of Derivatives (9): Try a plain vanilla, or maybe a
butterfly
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The astonishing growth of the emerging debt market has given birth to a new
generation of derivatives, says Ms Alexandra McLeod, of Bank of America,
Illinois. Plain vanilla put and call options and structures such as
straddles, strangles, bull spreads and butterflies are some of the exotic
names of products developed in the rocket science laboratories of the
world's leading investment banks
</TEXT>
