<HEADLINE>
FT  16 NOV 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico falls 1.1%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican stocks were hurt by political worries in connection with the
investigation surrounding the assassination of Mr Jose Francisco Ruiz
Massieu, secretary general of the ruling Institutional Rev-olutionary Party
(PRI), in September. At the close the IPC index was down 27.49 or 1.1 per
cent at 2,459.15.
The market turned negative after the man leading the investigation, Mr Mario
Ruiz Massieu, brother of the murdered official, accused two senior PRI
officials of trying to hinder his inquiry.
Investors were also concerned about the increase in US interest rates by the
Federal Reserve, fearing that this could lead to a repatriation of US funds.
Heavily weighted Telefonos de Mexico opened higher but quickly joined the
losers, shedding 0.22 per cent.
</TEXT>
