<HEADLINE>
FT  16 NOV 94 / International Company News: Profits and sales plunge at
Sumitomo Realty
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sumitomo Realty and Development, a Japanese property developer, saw sales
and profits plunge in the first six months to September due to sluggish
sales of high-margin condominiums, writes Emiko Terazono in Tokyo.
Non-consolidated recurring profits - before extraordinary items and tax -
fell 44.4 per cent to Y2.8bn (Dollars 28.7m), while sales nosedived 52.4 per
cent to Y90.4bn. After-tax profits plunged 68.2 per cent to Y1.2bn.
Part of the decline in revenue was attributed to the fact that in last
year's first half the company made a one-off sale of properties as it cut
its real estate inventories.
Operating profits rose 2.7 per cent to Y20.8bn as the company eliminated
Y8.1bn in aid to its financial subsidiary last year.
For the full year to next March, it forecasts a 13.3 per cent fall in
non-consolidated pre-tax profits to Y7.5bn on a 28.6 per cent drop in sales
to Y200bn.
