development company with another subsidiary. The company said it sold
Y14.66bn of marketable securities to offset the loss.
For the full year to March, Yamaha is forecasting recurring profits of Y4bn,
up 83 per cent on last year's actual Y2.19bn, and net profits 237 per cent
higher at Y2bn, against Y593m, on expected sales up 4 per cent to Y330bn
from Y316.18bn.
On the Tokyo stock exchange yesterday, Yamaha shares closed Y40 higher at
Y1,250.
The interim results were announced after the market had closed.
