<HEADLINE>
FT  16 NOV 94 / Airport reports passenger record
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY, Northern Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Manchester Airport yesterday reported record passenger figures of 1.4m for
October - 8 per cent up on October last year and more than the airport's
annual total 30 years ago.
The continuing growth brought the airport's moving annual total of
passengers carried to 14.72m, 12 per cent ahead of last year's total. The
airport expects to reach 15m passengers this year.
The increases came in spite of the withdrawal of British Airways' Los
Angeles service, Canadian Airlines' flights to Toronto, South African
Airways' Johannesburg service and the suspension until spring of American
Airlines' New York flights.
However, Aer Lingus has started a New York service from Manchester,
Uzbekistan Airways has a route to Tashkent and France's Regional airline has
started a service to Lille. The airport offers 175 destinations, flown by 95
airlines.
Frequencies were increased on services between Manchester and Rome,
Brussels, Amsterdam and Glasgow. Lauda Air will double its Vienna return
flights to two a day from next March.
</TEXT>
