FT  16 NOV 94 / Lottery ticket bonanza continues
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sales of National Lottery tickets continued yesterday at a level not far
behind Monday's total of 7.5m, Raymond Snoddy writes.
Camelot, the lottery operator, said that by 6pm last night a 14m Pounds 1
tickets had been sold in the lottery's first two days, far above
expectations.
The sales are being helped by enormous publicity before Saturday's first
multi-million pound jackpot draw. Camelot estimates that the top prize will
be at least Pounds 2m and if the current level of interest is sustained it
could be much higher.
After only two days of ticket sales the five causes that will benefit from
the lottery - arts, charities, national heritage, the millennium fund and
sport - are already guaranteed a total payment of about Pounds 4m.
