<HEADLINE>
FT  16 NOV 94 / Fall in water disconnections
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fewer households are being disconnected for failing to pay their water
bills, Ofwat, the industry's watchdog, said yesterday.
There were 5,532 domestic disconnections between April and September - a 7
per cent drop on the 5,924 in the same period last year. The number of
non-domestic disconnections fell by 3 per cent to 1,437.
